description.0: Devil must escape after a brutal attack from the Killer-Folk. Presuming Devil to be dead, Seven-Scars kidnaps Moon-Boy, holding him captive in a cave. Will Devil be able to find his friend before Seven-Scars performs a sacrifice with Moon-Boy and Long-Legs?
description.1: Just as Bruce is freed from the Hulk's curse, trouble arises at the Gamma Base. The Leader returns- and imprisons Colonel Ross and Doc Samson!
description.2: Iron Man and Jack of Hearts! Drawn from Earth to fight a deadly duel beyond the stars!
description.3: Thor, Iron Man and S.H.I.E.L.D. are prepared to annihilate F. A.U.S.T. But it's a Catch 22- attack and destroy the city, or don't attack and be destroyed!
description.4: Dracula is evil but he's about to face evil incarnate - Satan!
description.5: Thing finds himself caught in the crosshairs of Diablo and Dr. Doom...and is also reunited with an old friend long believed dead! While in Hollywood, Sue discovers that Reed is in peril with a simple phone call.
description.9: THE PHAROAH AND THE FORCE! Spider-Man along with members of the X-Men must fight alongside one another to stop the Living Pharoah who plans to use Havok as a human battery to amplify his powers.
description.10: Inside Devil-Slayer's dimension, Valkyrie and her new ally hunt down a Hulk… who's already engaged in battle!
description.11: Howard the Duck has a lot of his mind and decides to go for a walk and think things over. The life of a Duck isn't easy, and once again Howard gets himself into trouble on the mean streets of NYC. Will Howard the Duck ever catch a break?
description.12: The true identity of Green Goblin revealed! And the villain behind the mask is the last person you'd expect! What strange turn of events has led to this dual battle of the Goblins? And will Spider-Man be able to keep tabs on who's who? A shocking twist that will leave heads reeling!
description.13: The Avengers are joined by Ms. Marvel as they track Jocasta back to Ultron's lair. Will the team's combined might be enough to take down one of their greatest foes?
description.14: In the seeds of his past, Steve Rogers finds a perilous present! Watch Cap takes on the world in the Hour of the Hero!
description.16: Adapting Anthony Hope's The Prisoner of Zenda! A tale of swapped kings and stolen crowns!
description.20: Han and Chewie are captured by space pirates while Luke takes on a monstrous Sea-Dragon!
description.24: The Man-Thing is a prisoner of man! Peter Parker does the right thing when he returns the Man-Thing to its Floridian swamp after its unwilling exhibition in New York. Back in Citrusville, the Man-Thing is now free to pursue an old feud...
description.26: Doctor Strange's dreams foretell of a dark threat. Even the Eye of Agamotto can't detect this one!
description.27: Howard and the gang set out for Bzzk's Joh's Imperium Emporium to save Jennifer. Can Howard's monster squad handle Bzzk' Joh's fiends as they make their way through the dungeon?
description.28: The Behemoth, a giant reptilian monster, is on the rampage and Han Slo may be a small village's only hope.
description.29: Three of Edgar Allen Poe's thrilling short stories are brought to life in vivid (and spooky) detail. Collecting ""The Cask of Amontillado,"" "The Pit and the Pendulum," and ""The Tell-Tale Heart.""
description.30: The First Appearance of Devil Dinosaur!  Deep in the Valley of the Flame, Moon-Boy reveals the origins of Devil Dinosaur. Is the red-skinned and red-eyed Dino as menacing as the town-folk believe?
description.31: Doctor Strange—an enemy of Ghost Rider? A demonic “Strange” begins a sporadic attack on Johnny Blaze.
description.32: Bruce Banner is rescued by radioactive children. But little does he know...the children are cannibals- and he's on the menu!
description.33: Jack of Hearts becomes Iron Man's apprentice.
description.35: The first appearance of Mystique!  A fight to stop a kidnapping turns into a race-against-the-clock hostage situation! Can Ms. Marvel save Namorita from Tiger Shark before her oxygen supply runs out?
description.36: Spider-Woman swings in her first ongoing series! Jessica Drew's life has been marked by tragedy- her capture by Hydra, her entanglement with the High Evolutionary. But now, Jessica is determined to build a new life for herself in London. But with no sense of normalcy, it's not long before Jessica realizes that her spider self may be easier to handle than her humanity. Has the world turned against Spider-Woman? And who is Jerry Hunt, the S.H.I.E.L.D. agent who swears he's met Jessica before?
description.37: Thor is faced with a mysterious new enemy! Will Tony Stark have any insight on the identity of this mystery villain?
description.38: What if Electro revealed Matt Murdock's blindness? In this What If? Special, Daredevil's strongest weakness is exposed. Plus, an extra What If? featuring Spider-Man characters as farm animals!
description.39: While the X-Men try to relax and play a game of baseball, Warhawk enters the Danger Room to wreak havoc.
description.40: The team has split up, and each member is following their own bliss. Meanwhile, Ben is warned by a deceased friend that a NASA mission he is about to embark on is sabotaged- but is the source to be trusted?
description.44: After his tussle with Green Goblin, Spider-Man is tossed in a dumpster like Monday's trash! Will Peter Parker be able to abandon his alter-ego in time to save Aunt May? Or will Silvermane continue to deter Spidey from the most important mission of his life?
description.45: Jocasta re-awakens and is ready to take on all of the Avengers at once. Is the Bride of Ultron also connected to the disappearances of other Avengers members?
description.46: The past adventures of Captain America continue! With villains running amuck, Steve Rogers and Bucky Barnes scramble to stop the combined forces of Baron Zemo, Lyle Dekker, and the Red Skull!
description.53: Terror in the deep! Tiger Shark is on the hunt for Namorita!
description.54: Captain Marvel has fought lethal foes before, but never one quite like DEATHGRIP, whose very touch can shrivel Mar-Vell to dust!
description.55: It's the final showdown against Yellow Claw! ‘Nuff said!
description.58: Kraven the Hunter has snared Tigra in his clutches! And now, the feral cat-woman is being used as bait in a battle against Spider-Man! Will Spidey set Tigra loose before the fur really flies?
description.60: Howard and Man Thing team-up to try and stop new foe Bzzk'Joh! Will they be able to rescue Jennifer from their new all-powerful foe!?
description.61: When the High-hounds attack, a mythical monster is summoned that may mean the end for a village as well as Han and Chewie!
description.62: Adapting Robert Louis Stevenson's novel Kidnapped! Orphan David Balfour seeks his inheritance across the vast Scottish Highlands!
description.63: Aunt May's life hangs in the balance, and only Peter can save her! But with Spider-Man otherwise occupied at a mobster meeting, will the devastating news come too late? The Green Goblin continues to torment Spidey, but to what end?
description.64: Mad industrialist Jason Beere attacks the Avengers Mansion wearing an armored suit similar in design to Iron Man. When Beere is defeated by three members of the team, he reveals that he is dying and has rigged four bombs to explode when his heart stops beating! How will the Avengers save a man at the end of his rope? And how will they save the city at large?
description.65: Captain America, the hero! Captain America, the Sentinel of Liberty! Captain America, the movie star?
description.69: Heather Glenn learns Daredevil's true identity of Matt Murdock?and blames him for the death of her father?!
description.70: Bruce Banner is in for a surprise when he's stowed away on the ship of- The Stingray!
description.71: Iron Man, Yellowjacket, and Jack of Hearts attempt to revert Madame Masque back to her normal state.
description.72: The Stilt-Man is out of prison and ready to face the Mighty Thunderer! Get ready for their sky-scraping showdown!
description.73: Janus continues to take the fight to his father Dracula!
description.74: Johnny heads out West to pursue a career as a race car driver. But just because the FF have quit, doesn't mean the evil-doers have too!
description.77: Carol's father--in deadly danger! First in an accident, and then at the mercy of the sinister Steeplejack, only Ms. Marvel can save him twice in one day! But will that be enough to make him realize the error of his ignorant beliefs?
description.80: After being captured by Arcade, Spidey and Captain Britain end up in Murderworld - the unhappiest place on Earth!
description.84: Forced to join the S.O.O.F.I. (Save Our Offspring From Indecency) movement- Howard must stop the Supreme SOOFI! Using the Blanditron device, the Supreme SOOFI tries to control Howard's mind, but to no avail. How will Howard stop the S.O.O.F.I. movement?
description.85: Ghost Rider’s Hellfire cycle has gone missing! But by what magical means?
description.86: Captain Barracuda has captured Hulk and Crusoe, and the pirate has turned Crusoe into an ape! Can Hulk stop this piratical menace before he himself is turned into a gorilla?
description.87: Iron Man and Jack of Hearts battle Midas.
description.89: Damocles' Cobalt Cannon is just about finished- and will have the power to wipe out New York! Thor is aided by the villain's brother, who decides to take matters into his own hands!
description.90: What if Flash Thompson had been bitten by the radioactive spider? Flash Thompson as...Spider-Man! But without the scientific know-how of Peter Parker, will Thompson reach his full potential as the wall-crawler?
description.91: The X-Men return to Earth and take a much needed vacation.
description.92: It's an emotional breakup as each team member goes their separate ways. Will Sue shine as a siren of the Silver Screen? But first, the FF must take care of some last minute business!
description.95: Han and Chewie take a new job defending a moisture farmer from a local gang known as the Cloud-Riders.
description.99: The ancient world is embroiled in a mighty clash of armies; Greek versus Trojan. Helen, the most beautiful woman in the world, has betrayed her husband, the Greek, Menelaus, and fled to Troy with Trojan prince, Paris. The Greeks have sailed to Troy to bring her back... and crush all that stand in their way. It is a tale of gods and men... heroism and betrayal. Adapting Homer's epic The Iliad!

6.text: Spider-Man's putting Bobby Drake on ice! Iceman attacks Angel and Spidey when Stuart Clarke is incapacitated. Will Spidey be able to cool down his friend? And more importantly, will Peter get his story for the Daily Bugle?

8.text: The villain responsible for framing the Thing is revealed, and it happens to be a familiar face. How will the Thing take down this villain? With his allies Daredevil and the Avengers by his side, of course!

15.text: Machine Man pulls off impressive technological feats to escape the clutches of Colonel Kragg!

17.text: Get a rare glimpse at Shang-Chi's childhood in "Deadly Lesson: Like Father, Like Son…?"

21.text: A galactic battle to the death—and the prize is the gift of life! (note: this contains the Star-Lord story only)

22.text: Cap, Namor and the Torch scramble to rescue Bucky and Toro!

23.text: THING’S IN THE BIG HOUSE! Although everyone believes that Ben Grimm is guilty, Matt Murdock is convinced that Grimm is innocent, and he intends to prove it. However, Murdock finds that he must turn to his alter ego, Daredevil, to prove his friend’s innocence.

25.text: The fight against the In-Betweener becomes a battle of wits, when Strange has the ingenious idea to use his foe's masters against him!

35.text: A fight to stop a kidnapping turns into a race-against-the-clock hostage situation! Can Ms. Marvel save Namorita from Tiger Shark before her oxygen supply runs out?

41.text: Peter travels to Los Angeles to investigate the collapse of the Champions, L.A.'s own super hero team. But will former member Angel be forthcoming with answers? Plus, Rampage on the streets!

42.text: Absolved of the crimes that landed him in Seagate Penitentiary, Luke Cage celebrates at the penthouse suite of his lawyer. While there, Cage reflects on his past; Power Man’s origins revealed! However, this reverie is disturbed when criminals Stiletto and Discus crash the party!

43.text: Machine Man helps and befriends psychiatrist Peter Spaulding to get out of the woods safely. Meanwhile, Colonel Kragg and his men are out to terminate the last living X-51 unit…A.K.A., MACHINE MAN!

47.text: Shang-Chi battles the Cat and Skull-Crusher in "Hiding Cats!"

51.text: T’Challa’s returning to Wakanda and the timing couldn’t be better. Mutinous half-brother Jakarra has been mutated by Vibranium…and his coup for the throne is gaining fast momentum. Introducing the Wakandan Royal Family!

52.text: Dyna-Mite becomes the Mighty Destroyer II!

53.text: Terror in the deep! Tiger Shark is on the hunt for Namorita!

54.text: Captain Marvel has fought lethal foes before, but never one quite like DEATHGRIP, whose very touch can shrivel Mar-Vell to dust!

55.text: It's the final showdown against Yellow Claw! ‘Nuff said!

57.text: The Thing is being framed and faces the possibility of being thrown behind bars! The only man worthy of defending him is the Man Without Fear, Matt Murdock, the alter ego of Daredevil.

59.text: Ms. Marvel seeks the help of the Defenders when she has a vision that shows all of them are in trouble.

66.text: A savage new quest for Shang-Chi starts here!

69.text: Heather Glenn learns Daredevil's true identity of Matt Murdock…and blames him for the death of her father?!

75.text: While doling out a heroin bust, Spider-Man learns that a top-of-the-line officer is dealing with a personal crisis at home.

77.text: Carol's father--in deadly danger! First in an accident, and then at the mercy of the sinister Steeplejack, only Ms. Marvel can save him twice in one day! But will that be enough to make him realize the error of his ignorant beliefs?

78.text: The Thing, alongside Skull the Slayer, attempts to salvage a fallen plane. But with T-Rex and Brontosauruses hot on their trail, will these lost men, and woman, ever escape from the age of dinosaurs? Even more of a complication? Skull and his crew are under the thumb of the Jaguar Priest, savage king of this prehistoric world!

79.text: Our heroes must defeat the Scarlet Scarab!

82.text: Strange faces off against Creators member Stygyro to access the Wheel of Change. Later, Strange comes face-to-face with the In-Betweener to finish the job!

83.text: When Russian authorities detain the Defenders, Bruce Banner - the only one unaffected by the radiation - goes to the American ambassador for help freeing his team.

88.text: The Dire Wraiths are under the thumb of the ‘Big Man’…and only Brock Jones as the Torpedo can scramble his army!

93.text: After the Hate-Monger is revealed to be the Man-Beast in disguise, Spidey, Flash and Razorback must stop him and Brother Power.

94.text: Luke Cage teams up with former foes Misty Knight, Iron Fist, and Colleen Wing to rescue his friends from the Bushmaster! Traveling to the prison where Power Man once did time, the crew runs afoul of deadly inmates! To make matters worse, the heroes find the machine that gave Luke Cage his powers! And it’s been reactivated to serve the Bushmaster!

97.text: Shang-Chi takes on the Skull-Crusher, while several of his friends deal with personal blows in their love lives.
